      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Chris has spent much of his executive career in financial services. Most recently, he has specialised in digital transformation at scale, as Managing Director of the digital business of <abbr title="Royal Bank of Scotland">RBS</abbr>/NatWest, and then at Virgin Money. Prior to this, he held senior roles as a Strategy Director, Managing Director of a European consumer finance business and as an Operations Director.</p>

<p>Earlier in his career, Chris worked as a management consultant with Price Waterhouse.</p>

<p>Chris Morson was appointed a Non-Executive Board Member and Audit & Risk Committee member at DVLA in November 2013. He was re-appointed in November 2016.</p>

<p>He was appointed a Non-Executive Board Member at HM Land Registry in January 2018 and is currently interim chair of the Audit Committee and member of Remuneration Committee.</p>

<p>Chris is also a Non-Executive Director at the Money Advice Service, as well as Audit & Risk Committee and Nominations Committee member.</p>

<h2 id="education">Education</h2>

<p>Chris has a <abbr title="Bachelor of Science">BSc</abbr> in Economics and Accounting from Loughborough University and attended the London Business School finance programme. Chris holds an <abbr title="Master of Business Administration">MBA</abbr> with distinction from Cranfield, where he was awarded the Courage prize for overall performance and the Venture Capital prize.</p>

<p>Chris has also completed the Financial Times Non-Executive Directors diploma.</p>

</div>
      </section>

